Our Vision

At Route 183 Living, our vision is to build intentional communities that prioritize sustainability, community living and shared values. We strive to unlock the value of land while delivering value to the residents, creating spaces where individuals can live, work, and connect with others who share their vision for a better world.

We envision intentional communities that promote self-sufficiency, environmental stewardship and social responsibility. Our communities will be designed to encourage social interaction, community involvement, and shared responsibility, fostering a sense of belonging and connection among residents. We aim to expand our intentional communities globally, creating a network of sustainable, community-driven spaces that offer residents the opportunity to experience the benefits of intentional living in different parts of the world. By doing so, we hope to inspire a movement towards intentional living, creating a brighter, more connected, and sustainable future for all.

At the core of our vision is a commitment to delivering value to the community. We believe that by building intentional communities that prioritize sustainability and community involvement, we can create positive change that extends beyond the boundaries of our communities, impacting the wider world and inspiring others to follow in our footsteps.

Leadership

Our Leadership

Terry Hunter

President

Terry Hunter is a passionate and dedicated individual who grew up on a family farm in the community of Astle, New Brunswick. Holding degrees in both Social Sciences and Business, Terry is also a Certified Forest Technologist with specializing in reforestation and harvesting sustainable. With a personal vision to enable as many people as possible to adopt economically and environmentally sustainable practices. Terry combines his diverse educational background and experience to inspire change in industry and communities alike.

Norma Aziz

Vice President

Norma Aziz is a dynamic entrepreneur with an impressive track record in the transportation business and tourism industry. Her innovative spirit and keen business acumen has allowed her to create successful ventures that cater to the evolving needs of travelers and commuters alike. With a genuine passion for connecting people and places, Norma has made a significant impact on the way individuals experience and explore new destinations. Her commitment to excellence and customer satisfaction has garnered her a well-deserved reputation as a trailblazer in both the transportation and tourism sectors.

Lenzi Aziz

CFO

Lenzi Aziz currently living on active farm in New Brunswick. He has extensive experience in intelligence solutions in the Capital Markets with over 15 years experience in one of Canada's largest banks. Lenzi believes that intelligent solutions should be affordable, sustainable, and economically viable. Lenzi is passionate about blogging on topics that interest him, and he believes that affordable housing is an important issue that deserves attention. With his expertise and leadership skills, Lenzi is committed to making a positive impact in the world of business and beyond.
